summary: Eileen Gail Dinneen was an employee of the Select Committee on Assassinations (SCAS). She is listed in payroll and certification reports from April 1978, August 1978, and December 1978. These documents provide her name, and in some cases, her salary and social security number, indicating her role as a staff member within the committee during that period.
significance: Eileen Gail Dinneen's significance lies in her employment within the Select Committee on Assassinations. While the specific nature of her role isn't detailed in these documents, her presence on the payroll and certification reports confirms her involvement in the committee's operations during its investigation into the JFK assassination.
